charles h keating jr once called the rev jim bakker of 
american commerce is the latest of the high rollers to face 
criminal charges in the savings and loan fiasco 
other sampl officers had fleets of jets and yachts owned posh 
beach mansions ate in audy european restaurants threw outrageous 
parties and bought milliondollar paintings 
but it was keating who symbolized the sampl mess with his carefree 
lifestyle while he controlled lincoln savings and loan of irvine 
calif 
lincolns 1989 collapse the most expensive to date could cost 
taxpayers more than 2 billion to cover governmentguaranteed 
savings 
with the freewheeling keating at its helm since 1984 lincoln 
specialized in the sale of junk bonds for its parent company 
american continental corp it also financed such lavish ventures as 
a 900anight hotel 
he contributed 13 million to five us senators his salary in 
1986 and 1987 totaled 725 million although he now claims to be 
broke 
earlier this year us rep jim leach riowa called keating 
a fianciopath of obscene proportions the rev jim bakker of 
american commerce referring to the highprofile minister whos 
serving a 45year jail term for bilking 37 million from his 
followers 
on tuesday keating was indicted with three associates on 42 
counts of criminal fraud relating to the sale of 250 million of 
junk bonds prosecutors charge he violated california securities 
laws in defrauding more than 20000 investors 
the criminal charges are not his only legal problem 
federal regulators last year filed a 11 billion racketeering 
suit the largest bank fraud suit in us history to try to 
recover the money keating is alleged to have looted from lincoln 
last month federal officials also took legal action against 
keating and five of lincolns top officers in an attempt to recoup 
409 million in losses from three sour business deals 
keating has denied wrongdoing saying he is being singled out by 
malicious bureaucrats who dont understand the complexities of 
the financial deals he attempted 
the lincoln failure is part of an sampl debacle that could cost 
taxpayers 500 billion with interest over 40 years 
leach a member of the house banking committee called it the 
biggest bank heist in history one that goes beyond the bank 
vaults to pick the pocket of every american 
others like keating who face charges or investigations 
edwin fast eddie mcbirney was indicted in july on 17 
counts of bank fraud and other charges for the way he ran sunbelt 
savings association also known as gunbelt savings in dallas its 
failure in 1988 could cost the taxpayers 2 billion 
federal prosecutors said he spent 13 million on halloween and 
christmas parties in 1984 and 1985 at a 1984 halloween bash in his 
back yard mcbirney dressed up as a king and served his guests 
antelope and lion meat 
the government also said an audience of sunbelt executives and 
borrowers hired las vegas prostitutes as striptease dancers who 
engaged in sex acts with them 
don dixon was indicted in june on 38 conspiracy and fraud 
counts in the 1987 collapse of the vernon savings and loan in 
vernon texas which will cost taxpayers at least 13 billion 
the government said dixon used sampl funds to pay for political 
contributions hire prostitutes take hunting trips and rent a 
beach home the sampl had a luxury yacht and a fleet of five planes 
worth 6 million it also paid the 22000 tab for dixons 
gastronomic tour of european restaurants 
eight vernon officers have already been convicted including 
chairman woody lemons who began serving a 30year jail term in 
june the sentence is the stiffest to date for an sampl officer 
dl danny faulkner of the empire sampl in mesquite texas 
and six other defendants were charged with fraudulently inflating 
land values in a 135 million condominium deal north of dallas 
their first trial ended in a hung jury last year a second trial 
is pending 
prosecutors said they lavished themselves with jets expensive 
watches and a 4 million mansion faulkner reportedly gave mink 
coats and mercedes cars as christmas gifts he tipped waitresses 
100 
in florida david paul has not been charged with breaking the 
law but he was ousted during a federal takeover this year of 
centrust in miami floridas largest thrift after the state 
alleged he inappropriately spent 45 million of centrusts money 
paul imported six french chefs for a 1988 dinner of truffle soup 
and beluga caviar decorated his home with a 132 million painting 
by peter paul reubens that was paid for with sampl money entertained 
actress elizabeth taylor with a party aboard his 7 million yacht 
drove a mercedes limo and had a boat called bodacious 
